  Key design points:
    - Closed RedactionProfile enum with serde rename to exact §14 wire names (default/strict/debug_capture).
    - Per-RecordType bucketing via record_category() over RecordType::as_wire_str() prefix matching — 6 categories (Lifecycle/Vault/Recovery/Telemetry/Segment/Generic). Avoids 427-arm match while staying coherent with spec wire-name namespacing.
    - normalize_key() handles hyphen/space/dot/camelCase variants so x-api-key, Authorization, clientSecret all match.
    - Strict on Lifecycle/Telemetry/Generic -> reduce_to_structural_marker: { record_type, payload_hash_prefix (BLAKE3-truncated 32 hex), redacted_under_profile: "strict" }. Recovery+Segment kept verbatim. Vault hashes PII keys, keeps capability metadata.
    - Default+DebugCapture share the secret-redaction body transformation per spec §14 ("minimal redaction; only secrets" applies to both); operational distinction is policy-attested via the redaction_profile field. Asserted as the design rule, not a bug.
    - Redaction applied in seal_inner BEFORE content_hash + signature -- constitutional anchor §14 ("no unredacted-but-signed representation anywhere").
    - ReceiptForSigning includes redaction_profile so tampering with the profile post-seal breaks signature verification (test t013_tampering_redaction_profile_breaks_signature).
    - EvidenceReceipt.redaction_profile has #[serde(default)] for back-compat with pre-T-013 receipt JSON (test t013_legacy_receipt_json_without_profile_field_deserializes_with_default).
    - Proto AppendRequest NOT mutated (per STOP rule); server-side defaults to RedactionProfile::Default. gRPC integration test verifies the wire envelope reflects "default" at proto field tag 14.
