    - RocksDB: list_sealed_segments scans chain_index→segments CFs (sync DB read); compact_segment is one atomic WriteBatch (delete receipt rows + record_type_index rows; set compacted_at::<seg_id> sentinel in metadata CF); segment row in segments CF untouched so recover_sealed_chain on reopen continues to verify. emit_approval_required uses blocking_write on the open-segment state. Helper rocksdb_segment_compacted_at(db, seg_id) introspects the sentinel.
