    - RecordType +1: CompactionApprovalRequired (wire ID 1000, retention FOREVER). Proto IDL: COMPACTION_APPROVAL_REQUIRED = 1000; reserved range tightened to 1001..9999. Total RecordType variants = 428 (Wave 13 dense 1..=427 + Wave 14+ reserved 1 = 428). Multiple invariant tests updated (record_type_count, every_variant_round_trips, wave_id ranges split into Wave 13 dense + Wave 14+ reserved, etc.).
    - New encoding helper metadata_compacted_at_key(&SegmentId) returning the `compacted_at::<id>` key for the metadata CF. Compaction state lives OUT of the segments CF on purpose so segment-row byte layout is unchanged and §11.4 cryptographic recovery is untouched.
    - Privacy ceiling: CompactionApprovalRequired added to is_constitutionally_public_record_type() — operators always see compaction governance events.
